<br>
I think war with Iraq is likely not because its necessary for the &quot;safety of the world&quot; or any such BS reason.<br>
<br>
Revenge is one of the main reasons folks.  We failed getting Osama, and Afganistan was hardly a &quot;satisfying&quot; war.  The general populace is not satisified!  We need more death, more killing.  Eye for an eye.  Where does it stop?  <br>
<br>
Economics is another reason.  We'd love to set up some dummy admin in Iraq and have unlimited cheap oil.  TELL ME that has not been discussed in upper circles.  Of course it has.<br>
<br>
Although, I think the reason why this is so important to Bush (and really he is THE MAIN DRIVING FORCE BEHIND THIS WHOLE DISCUSSION), is cuz he wants to fix daddy's mistake of 10 years ago... and this is his excuse to do it.<br>
<br>
Makes me sad and embarassed.  When I talk to foreign friends in game about this and other similar matters, I don't find myself defending Bush, or the actions of our leadership.  I find myself defending the average American with thoughts and ideas and wishes for peace.  Ideas and opinions which even our &quot;FREEDOM OF PRESS&quot; tends to filter out.<br>
<br>
Yea, we have freedom of press to cover whatever they want.  But our media is so biased.  Our media WANTS another war.  They have an interest in promoting only one side of the story.  Death and war is a big viewership draw.<br>
<br>
So anyway, for all you foreign people that watch CNN and go WTF?  I apologize on behalf of the idiocy of Bush, the media, and our country.  Americans aren't mindless sheep that follow where lead.  There is a VERY large percentage of folks that think our whole course of action is leading to disaster - you just don't get the opportunity to see it on TV.<br>
<br>
/cry.  Now I'm depressed. <p>Mokindank Dankmoka<br>
