I don't think you should use christian principles or any religious ideals to support politicaly charged statements.  Everyone knows religion can be manipulated when necessary; always allowing one to do certain deeds while still in god's favour.<br>
<br>
There were factions opposed to slavery during the times, but they didn't have sufficient political power at first to denounce it.  Slavery has been an extremely commonplace occurence around the world in one way or another.  America just happened to be a nation that prolonged the use of slaves in the public eye.  If anything, I would argue the segregation of the people was more of a taint on the freedoms boasted by the new land than the actual act of slavery.  Once slavery was abolished, people should have known better and treated each other as humans rather than by race.....but that's something that will always happen. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a> <b>3</b> <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=141&stop=160>8</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=161&stop=180>9</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=181&stop=200>10</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=201&stop=220>11</a><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showMessageRange?topicID=171.topic&start=221&stop=221>12</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"